info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 09 at 11:20PM CDT until April 10 at 10:32PM CDT by NWS Sioux Falls
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in South Dakota...Minnesota... Big Sioux River below Dell Rapids affecting Minnehaha County. Rock River at Luverne affecting Rock County. Big Sioux River near Trent affecting Moody County. Sixmile Creek near Brookings affecting Brookings County. ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Iowa... South Dakota... Big Sioux River above Hawarden affecting Sioux, Union and Lincoln Counties. Big Sioux River near Brookings affecting Brookings and Moody Counties. Big Sioux River at Akron affecting Plymouth and Union Counties. Split Rock Creek near Corson affecting Minnehaha County. Rock River at Rock Rapids affecting Lyon County. ...FLOOD WARNING FOR SNOWMELT NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE TOMORROW EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Rock River at Luverne. * WHEN...Until late tomorrow evening. * IMPACTS...At 10.0 feet, significant agricultural flooding begins. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 10:30 PM CDT Sunday the stage was 10.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 10:30 PM CDT Sunday was 10.0 feet. - Forecast...The river may continue to rise to near 10.5 ft by Monday morning. - Flood stage is 10.0 feet. && Fld Observed Forecasts (1 am CDT) Location Stg Stg Day/Time Tue Wed Thu Rock River Luverne 10.0 10.0 Sun 10 pm MSG MSG MSG &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Monday morning.
